  "text": "Focusing on the third step above, where the mixing matrix already has orthogonal columns, ICA algorithms already suffer dramatically from the presence of heavy-tailed data. As proposed in [CITATION_1] , Gaussian damping is a preprocessing technique that converts data from an ICA model X = AS, where A is unitary (columns are orthogonal with unit l 2 -norm) to data from a related ICA model X R = AS R , where R > 0 is a parameter to be chosen. The independent components of S R have finite moments of all orders and so the existing algorithms can estimate A.",
