      "span_text": "As proposed in [CITATION_1] , Gaussian damping is a preprocessing technique that converts data from an ICA model X = AS, where A is unitary (columns are orthogonal with unit l 2 -norm) to data from a related ICA model X R = AS R , where R > 0 is a parameter to be chosen."
